step.context:
\text{If }I=\int \sqrt{\sin 2 x} \cdot \cos 2 x  \,dx
= \int \dfrac{1}{2} \sqrt{t}\, dt \\
\text{then does this look correct?}

step.tex:
\begin{align}
  I &= \int  \dfrac{1}{2} \sqrt{t} \, dt   = \dfrac{1}{2} \int  \sqrt{t} \, dt  \\
    &= \dfrac{1}{2} \left[ \frac{t^{3/2}}{3/2} \right] + C 
   = \dfrac{1}{3} t^{3/2} + C \\
    &= \dfrac{1}{3} (\sin 2 x)^{3/2} + C    
\end{align}

\begin{align}
  I &= \int  \dfrac{1}{2} \sqrt{t} \, dt   = \dfrac{1}{2} \int  \sqrt{t} \, dt  \\
    &= \dfrac{1}{2} \cdot {t^{3/2}} + C  \\
    &= \dfrac{1}{2} (\sin 2 x)^{3/2} + C

\end{align}
